{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Mapped Types"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "mapped type",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " iterates over the keys of an existing type and produces a new type where each key's value type can be transformed. The syntax "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{ [K in keyof T]: ... }",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " creates a type with the same keys as "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "T",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " but with new value types. Mapped types are the foundation of most TypeScript utility types."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Mapped type anatomy: [K in keyof T]?: SomeType<T[K]> with labels for each part and key modifiers",
          "title": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Basic Mapped Type Syntax"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "interface User {\n  id: number;\n  name: string;\n  email: string;\n}\n\n// Copy every key and value as-is (identity mapped type)\ntype Copy<T> = { [K in keyof T]: T[K] };\ntype UserCopy = Copy<User>; // { id: number; name: string; email: string }\n\n// Make every value nullable\ntype Nullable<T> = { [K in keyof T]: T[K] | null };\ntype NullableUser = Nullable<User>;\n// { id: number | null; name: string | null; email: string | null }\n\n// Wrap every value in an array\ntype Arrayed<T> = { [K in keyof T]: T[K][] };\ntype ArrayedUser = Arrayed<User>;\n// { id: number[]; name: string[]; email: string[] }\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Modifier Operators: + and -"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "TypeScript allows adding or removing "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "?",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (optional) and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "readonly",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " modifiers inside a mapped type. Prefix a modifier with "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "-",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " to remove it, or "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "+",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (the default) to add it. These four operations cover all combinations needed to make types more or less strict."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "interface Config {\n  host: string;\n  port: number;\n  debug?: boolean;\n  readonly apiKey: string;\n}\n\n// Make all properties optional (equivalent to Partial<T>)\ntype AllOptional<T> = { [K in keyof T]+?: T[K] };\ntype PartialConfig = AllOptional<Config>;\n// { host?: string; port?: number; debug?: boolean; readonly apiKey?: string }\n\n// Remove optional from all properties (equivalent to Required<T>)\ntype AllRequired<T> = { [K in keyof T]-?: T[K] };\ntype RequiredConfig = AllRequired<Config>;\n// { host: string; port: number; debug: boolean; readonly apiKey: string }\n\n// Make all properties readonly (equivalent to Readonly<T>)\ntype AllReadonly<T> = { +readonly [K in keyof T]: T[K] };\n\n// Remove readonly from all properties (Mutable<T> \u2014 not in stdlib)\ntype Mutable<T> = { -readonly [K in keyof T]: T[K] };\ntype MutableConfig = Mutable<Config>;\n// { host: string; port: number; debug?: boolean; apiKey: string }\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key Remapping with as"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "TypeScript 4.1+ added "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "key remapping",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " via "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "as",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " in the mapped type. This lets you rename keys, filter out keys (map to "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "never",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "), or derive new key names from existing ones using template literal types."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "interface User {\n  id: number;\n  name: string;\n  email: string;\n}\n\n// Rename every key to its uppercase version\ntype UppercaseKeys<T> = { [K in keyof T as Uppercase<K & string>]: T[K] };\ntype UpperUser = UppercaseKeys<User>;\n// { ID: number; NAME: string; EMAIL: string }\n\n// Prefix every key with 'get'\ntype Getters<T> = {\n  [K in keyof T as `get${Capitalize<K & string>}`]: () => T[K]\n};\ntype UserGetters = Getters<User>;\n// { getId: () => number; getName: () => string; getEmail: () => string }\n\n// Filter keys \u2014 map to never to exclude\ntype OnlyStringValues<T> = {\n  [K in keyof T as T[K] extends string ? K : never]: T[K]\n};\ntype StringFields = OnlyStringValues<User>;\n// { name: string; email: string }  \u2014 id excluded (number)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Built-in Utility Types Based on Mapped Types"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "TypeScript's standard utility types are all implemented as mapped types:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// From the TypeScript standard library \u2014 all mapped types\ntype Partial<T>    = { [P in keyof T]+?: T[P] };\ntype Required<T>   = { [P in keyof T]-?: T[P] };\ntype Readonly<T>   = { +readonly [P in keyof T]: T[P] };\ntype Record<K extends keyof any, T> = { [P in K]: T };\ntype Pick<T, K extends keyof T>   = { [P in K]: T[P] };\ntype Omit<T, K extends keyof any> = Pick<T, Exclude<keyof T, K>>;\n\n// Usage with a real type:\ninterface Todo {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  done: boolean;\n  priority: 'low' | 'medium' | 'high';\n}\n\ntype TodoPreview   = Pick<Todo, 'id' | 'title'>;    // { id: number; title: string }\ntype TodoDraft     = Omit<Todo, 'id'>;               // { title: string; done: boolean; priority: ... }\ntype TodoPartial   = Partial<Todo>;                  // all properties optional\ntype TodoRecord    = Record<string, Todo>;           // { [key: string]: Todo }\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Homomorphic vs Non-Homomorphic Mapped Types"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "homomorphic mapped type",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " maps over "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "keyof T",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2014 it preserves modifiers ("
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "readonly",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "?",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ") from the original type. A "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "non-homomorphic mapped type",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " iterates over a different key set (e.g. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "string",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " or a union literal) and does not preserve modifiers."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "interface Profile {\n  readonly id: string;\n  name?: string;\n}\n\n// HOMOMORPHIC \u2014 maps over keyof Profile, preserves modifiers\ntype H = { [K in keyof Profile]: string };\n// { readonly id: string; name?: string }  \u2190 modifiers preserved!\n\n// NON-HOMOMORPHIC \u2014 maps over a literal union, no modifier preservation\ntype N = { [K in 'id' | 'name']: string };\n// { id: string; name: string }  \u2190 no readonly, no optional\n\n// Record<K, V> is non-homomorphic (K is not keyof anything)\ntype R = Record<'id' | 'name', string>;\n// { id: string; name: string }  \u2190 no modifiers\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Combining Mapped and Conditional Types"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Mapped and conditional types compose naturally. The value type in a mapped type can be a conditional type, enabling per-key transformations that depend on the original value type."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// Replace function properties with their return type\ntype UnwrapMethods<T> = {\n  [K in keyof T]: T[K] extends (...args: unknown[]) => infer R ? R : T[K]\n};\n\ninterface Service {\n  name: string;\n  getUser(id: string): Promise<User>;\n  getCount(): number;\n}\n\ntype ServiceResult = UnwrapMethods<Service>;\n// { name: string; getUser: Promise<User>; getCount: number }\n\n// Make properties optional only when they extend a certain type\ntype OptionalStrings<T> = {\n  [K in keyof T]: T[K] extends string ? T[K] | undefined : T[K]\n};\n\n// Convert all Date properties to string (for JSON serialization shape)\ntype Serialized<T> = {\n  [K in keyof T]: T[K] extends Date ? string : T[K]\n};\n\ninterface Event {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  createdAt: Date;\n  updatedAt: Date;\n}\ntype SerializedEvent = Serialized<Event>;\n// { id: number; title: string; createdAt: string; updatedAt: string }\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Mapped Types in Angular"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Form Group Typing"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Angular Reactive Forms work best with typed form groups. Mapped types let you derive the form control structure from a plain data model:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import { FormControl, FormGroup } from '@angular/forms';\n\n// Derive a FormGroup type from a data model\ntype FormControls<T> = {\n  [K in keyof T]: FormControl<T[K]>\n};\n\ninterface UserForm {\n  name: string;\n  email: string;\n  age: number;\n}\n\ntype UserFormControls = FormControls<UserForm>;\n// { name: FormControl<string>; email: FormControl<string>; age: FormControl<number> }\n\n// Build a typed form group factory\nfunction buildForm<T extends object>(\n  defaults: T\n): FormGroup<FormControls<T>> {\n  const controls = Object.fromEntries(\n    Object.entries(defaults).map(([k, v]) => [k, new FormControl(v)])\n  ) as FormControls<T>;\n  return new FormGroup(controls);\n}\n\nconst form = buildForm<UserForm>({ name: '', email: '', age: 0 });\nform.controls.name.setValue('Alice'); // typed: only string allowed\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Store State Selectors"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// Derive typed selector functions from a state interface\ntype Selectors<State> = {\n  [K in keyof State as `select${Capitalize<K & string>}`]: (state: State) => State[K]\n};\n\ninterface AppState {\n  users: User[];\n  loading: boolean;\n  error: string | null;\n}\n\ntype AppSelectors = Selectors<AppState>;\n// {\n//   selectUsers:   (state: AppState) => User[];\n//   selectLoading: (state: AppState) => boolean;\n//   selectError:   (state: AppState) => string | null;\n// }\n\n// Auto-generate selectors at runtime\nfunction createSelectors<State extends object>(state: State): Selectors<State> {\n  return Object.fromEntries(\n    Object.keys(state as object).map(k => [\n      `select${k[0].toUpperCase()}${k.slice(1)}`,\n      (s: State) => s[k as keyof State]\n    ])\n  ) as Selectors<State>;\n}\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "HTTP Patch Payload"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// A PATCH endpoint only requires the fields being updated\ntype PatchPayload<T> = Partial<Omit<T, 'id' | 'createdAt' | 'updatedAt'>>;\n\ninterface Product {\n  id: string;\n  name: string;\n  price: number;\n  stock: number;\n  createdAt: Date;\n  updatedAt: Date;\n}\n\ntype ProductPatch = PatchPayload<Product>;\n// { name?: string; price?: number; stock?: number }\n\nclass ProductService {\n  update(id: string, patch: ProductPatch): Observable<Product> {\n    return this.http.patch<Product>(`/api/products/${id}`, patch);\n  }\n}\n// TypeScript ensures the caller can only pass valid patchable fields\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "{ [K in keyof T]: T[K] }",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " is the core mapped type \u2014 iterate over keys, transform value types."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Use "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "-?",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " / "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "+?",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " and "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "-readonly",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " / "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "+readonly",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " to add or remove modifiers."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Key remapping with "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "as",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " lets you rename or filter keys (map to "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "never",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " to exclude)."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  "Homomorphic mapped types (over keyof T) preserve source modifiers; non-homomorphic ones do not."
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  "Built-in utilities like Partial, Required, Readonly, Pick, Omit, and Record are all implemented as mapped types."
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  "Combine with conditional types to apply per-key transformations based on the value type."
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  "In Angular, mapped types underpin typed reactive forms, state selectors, and HTTP patch payload typing."
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}